<b>Luffy's Country</b>

184
00:11:21.990 --> 00:11:27.340
<b>Ace's Country</b>

185
00:11:25.150 --> 00:11:27.760
What is it this time?!

186
00:11:27.760 --> 00:11:32.000
I'm gonna learn to survive on my own.
You guys can be Dadan's country.

187
00:11:32.970 --> 00:11:34.610
I'll borrow the bath sometimes.

188
00:11:34.610 --> 00:11:38.520
<b>Ace's Country</b>
<b>Luffy's Country</b>

189
00:11:59.700 --> 00:12:02.940
Ace! Help me out! It's a bear!

190
00:12:03.900 --> 00:12:06.400
You said you'd survive on your own, right?!

191
00:12:09.010 --> 00:12:10.300
Dammit!

192
00:12:20.360 --> 00:12:21.590
Luffy!

193
00:12:33.730 --> 00:12:36.120
Hey! Dadan's country! Anyone there?!

194
00:12:36.120 --> 00:12:39.420
Luffy got hurt! He needs first aid!

195
00:12:41.010 --> 00:12:43.920
Magra! Please, help Luffy!

196
00:12:43.920 --> 00:12:46.510
Take it easy! Hurry! Bring him in!

197
00:12:59.340 --> 00:13:02.720
Now, take it easy. This is no joke.

198
00:13:02.720 --> 00:13:07.130
If his wounds were any deeper,
it could've been fatal!

199
00:13:09.320 --> 00:13:12.400
You used to take on those
wild beasts as a trio, right?

200
00:13:14.760 --> 00:13:16.120
It's my fault!

201
00:13:17.400 --> 00:13:23.010
I should've learned by now that fighting
on your own doesn't prove that you're strong!

202
00:13:24.600 --> 00:13:27.090
I'm no good!

203
00:13:27.090 --> 00:13:29.260
No good at all!

204
00:13:32.770 --> 00:13:34.190
Ace...

205
00:13:34.190 --> 00:13:36.890
I'm so sorry, Luffy!

206
00:13:37.820 --> 00:13:38.660
I'm sorry!

207
00:13:48.610 --> 00:13:50.480
Hey, you guys!

208
00:13:50.980 --> 00:13:54.650
Makino came all the way
out here to bring us some drinks!

209
00:13:55.430 --> 00:13:58.380
You want to learn how to thank someone?

210
00:13:58.770 --> 00:14:00.100
Uh-huh.

211
00:14:00.100 --> 00:14:02.120
What's gotten into you?

212
00:14:02.120 --> 00:14:04.660
Seeing as I'm Luffy's big brother and all,

213
00:14:04.660 --> 00:14:11.860
I'd like to meet this Captain Red Hair someday
and properly thank him for everything he did for Luffy.

214
00:14:20.580 --> 00:14:22.340
Say something, will you?!

215
00:14:23.720 --> 00:14:25.540
I'm sorry.

216
00:14:25.540 --> 00:14:28.140
Okay then, I'll teach you.

217
00:14:28.140 --> 00:14:30.550
So, first of all...

218
00:14:30.550 --> 00:14:32.750
It's a dine and dash!

219
00:14:32.750 --> 00:14:34.980
Stop!

220
00:14:36.980 --> 00:14:40.360
Oh, we're forgetting something important!

221
00:14:40.360 --> 00:14:41.930
Oh, right...!

222
00:14:46.060 --> 00:14:48.470
– Thanks for the food!
– Thanks for the food!

223
00:14:48.470 --> 00:14:51.140
Shut up, you damn kids! Just pay the bill!

224
00:14:54.440 --> 00:14:56.590
I'm gonna win today!

225
00:15:32.090 --> 00:15:33.720
– Alright!
– Alright!

226
00:15:33.720 --> 00:15:35.720
Tonight, we're having bear stew!

227
00:16:35.260 --> 00:16:39.930
<b>7 Years Later</b>

228
00:16:41.280 --> 00:16:45.700
<b>Ace, 17 Years Old</b>

229
00:16:47.020 --> 00:16:51.690
<b>Luffy, 14 Years Old</b>

230
00:17:04.190 --> 00:17:06.200
Take care, Ace!

231
00:17:06.200 --> 00:17:10.140
Will do! See you later, Luffy!
I'm heading out now!

232
00:17:10.140 --> 00:17:15.550
Yeah! And I'll be a lot stronger
when I set out in three years!

233
00:17:21.990 --> 00:17:25.130
Give it your all, Ace!

234
00:17:25.130 --> 00:17:26.880
Take care of yourself!

235
00:17:26.880 --> 00:17:28.790
Try not to catch a cold!

236
00:17:28.790 --> 00:17:32.610
Just you wait! I'll make
a name for myself real soon!

237
00:17:34.090 --> 00:17:38.390
Ace, the son of the Pirate King,
grew up in complete secrecy...

238
00:17:38.390 --> 00:17:43.010
and quiety departed from
the shore near Mt. Colubo.

239
00:17:59.300 --> 00:18:01.210
There he goes!

240
00:18:01.910 --> 00:18:05.400
Honestly. How is Garp going to take this?

241
00:18:23.780 --> 00:18:25.960
You're gonna raise him, Dadan!

242
00:18:25.960 --> 00:18:29.290
No, wait! Whose kid is that?!

243
00:18:29.920 --> 00:18:32.200
Boss...

244
00:18:32.200 --> 00:18:34.730
Ace just left.

245
00:18:35.710 --> 00:18:37.220
Did he, now?

246
00:18:38.130 --> 00:18:41.460
But I'll be the one Garp chews out...

247
00:18:41.460 --> 00:18:43.910
What a hopeless little shit.

248
00:18:43.910 --> 00:18:48.010
Oh, and Ace left a message for you!

249
00:18:48.010 --> 00:18:53.100
What?! He's finally gone
and he's still complaining?!

250
00:18:53.100 --> 00:18:55.750
He said, "Thank you for everything."

251
00:19:01.220 --> 00:19:04.790
Give me a break! That idiot!

252
00:19:05.750 --> 00:19:08.540
What? Boss, are you crying?

253
00:19:08.540 --> 00:19:10.960
I'm not crying, you idiot!

254
00:19:23.270 --> 00:19:25.720
Only three more years for me!

255
00:19:26.300 --> 00:19:27.860
Gum-Gum...

256
00:19:28.140 --> 00:19:29.440
Pistol!

257
00:19:32.790 --> 00:19:36.140
Damn... Just a little off...

258
00:19:37.900 --> 00:19:42.060
That was close, Luffy!
Try lowering your center of gravity.

259
00:19:46.700 --> 00:19:48.560
Gum-Gum...

260
00:19:48.800 --> 00:19:49.980
Pistol!

261
00:20:03.650 --> 00:20:05.120
I wanna get stronger!

262
00:20:05.750 --> 00:20:09.160
And stronger!

263
00:20:09.290 --> 00:20:11.520
<b>Several Months Later</b>

264
00:20:16.880 --> 00:20:18.400
Luffy!

265
00:20:18.400 --> 00:20:20.330
Look at the newspaper!

266
00:20:20.330 --> 00:20:21.750
What's up?

267
00:20:21.750 --> 00:20:23.740
Just look!

268
00:20:23.740 --> 00:20:26.700
So cool! Ace made a name for himself!

269
00:20:26.700 --> 00:20:29.090
It's a picture of his pirate ship and crew!

270
00:20:29.090 --> 00:20:33.020
Amazing! Ace is amazing!

271
00:20:34.450 --> 00:20:36.770
But I'm not gonna lose to him!

272
00:20:40.740 --> 00:20:44.720
<b>3 Years Later</b>
<b>Luffy, 17 Years Old</b>

273
00:20:44.720 --> 00:20:46.590
Hey, come on!

274
00:20:46.590 --> 00:20:49.540
I'm leaving now. You're not gonna see me off?

275
00:20:49.540 --> 00:20:51.100
Hey!

276
00:20:51.100 --> 00:20:52.900
Shut up...!

277
00:20:53.120 --> 00:20:55.370
The mayor and Makino are okay with us,

278
00:20:55.370 --> 00:21:00.240
but we'd send the rest of Windmill Village
into a panic if we came down the mountain!

279
00:21:00.240 --> 00:21:01.440
But...

280
00:21:01.960 --> 00:21:03.970
Just get going already!

281
00:21:04.420 --> 00:21:07.520
Oh, okay. Well then, guys...

282
00:21:07.520 --> 00:21:09.780
Thanks for everything!

283
00:21:09.780 --> 00:21:12.900
Oh, don't embarrass us.
No need for thanks.

284
00:21:12.900 --> 00:21:15.460
Take it easy and take care.

285
00:21:15.460 --> 00:21:17.460
Yep! Sure thing!

286
00:21:19.220 --> 00:21:20.660
Oh, right!

287
00:21:21.250 --> 00:21:24.270
Dadan, I hate mountain bandits...

288
00:21:24.270 --> 00:21:25.900
Shut up, you little turd!

289
00:21:27.050 --> 00:21:29.800
...but I like you guys!

290
00:21:33.140 --> 00:21:36.910
Don't say dumb stuff like that!
Just get lost already, dammit!

291
00:21:36.910 --> 00:21:41.310
Sheesh! Every last one of you...!

292
00:21:42.130 --> 00:21:43.840
What, are you crying?

293
00:21:43.840 --> 00:21:46.450
No! I'm absolutely not!

294
00:21:47.950 --> 00:21:52.450
Windmill Village, at the outskirts of
the Kingdom of Goa on Dawn Island...

295
00:21:52.890 --> 00:21:56.890
Hey! You're going out to sea, so just
take my old fishing boat, Luffy!

296
00:21:56.890 --> 00:21:59.430
You'll sink right away in that thing!

297
00:21:59.430 --> 00:22:01.480
A rowboat? C'mon!

298
00:22:02.280 --> 00:22:05.900
Seriously, I'm fine with this!
It's the start of my journey!

299
00:22:09.810 --> 00:22:12.310
Sabo!

300
00:22:12.710 --> 00:22:18.050
Watch over me! I'm gonna set out to sea now!

301
00:22:20.110 --> 00:22:23.220
Sabo was first. Ace was second.

302
00:22:24.280 --> 00:22:27.230
I'm third, but I won't lose to them!

303
00:22:27.230 --> 00:22:31.460
Wait for me, Ace!
I'll catch up to you soon enough!

304
00:22:31.460 --> 00:22:34.480
What're you doing, Luffy,
shouting to yourself like that?

305
00:22:34.480 --> 00:22:36.640
Is it some sort of good luck charm?

306
00:22:36.640 --> 00:22:38.800
It's not a charm. It's a challenge!

307
00:22:39.140 --> 00:22:41.020
Who's Ace?

308
00:22:41.020 --> 00:22:41.770
Not a clue.

309
00:22:41.770 --> 00:22:44.210
Alright, I'm outta here!

310
00:22:53.310 --> 00:22:56.350
Well, Mayor, he's finally off.

311
00:22:56.350 --> 00:22:58.260
I'm gonna miss him.

312
00:22:58.260 --> 00:23:01.140
He's disgracing our village
by becoming a pirate!

313
00:23:04.130 --> 00:23:09.100
What a nice day to set sail!

314
00:23:21.320 --> 00:23:22.650
Th-That's...!

315
00:23:27.140 --> 00:23:29.550
If it isn't the Lord of the Coast.

316
00:23:34.960 --> 00:23:37.310
You don't know who you're messing with.

317
00:23:37.730 --> 00:23:40.670
Check out this technique
ten years in the making!

318
00:23:41.940 --> 00:23:44.400
Gum-Gum...

319
00:23:50.110 --> 00:23:52.000
Pistol!

320
00:24:08.890 --> 00:24:10.960
That'll teach you! Damn fish!

321
00:24:18.590 --> 00:24:22.470
Incredible! He beat the
Lord of the Coast with one punch!

322
00:24:23.940 --> 00:24:26.480
He's sure grown strong.

323
00:24:28.190 --> 00:24:30.280
First, I've gotta gather a crew.

324
00:24:30.280 --> 00:24:32.890
Ten people oughta do it!

325
00:24:33.530 --> 00:24:36.160
I'll also need a Jolly Roger!

326
00:24:36.960 --> 00:24:41.960
Alright! Let's go!

327
00:24:41.960 --> 00:24:43.830
I'm gonna be...

328
00:24:45.660 --> 00:24:48.160
King of the Pirates!

329
00:24:58.220 --> 00:24:59.880
We return to the present.

330
00:25:01.790 --> 00:25:07.260
His brother Ace is dead,
and Luffy mourns his loss.

331
00:25:20.810 --> 00:25:22.670
Luffy...

332
00:25:22.670 --> 00:25:25.900
Me, the King of the Pirates?!

333
00:25:25.900 --> 00:25:27.260
I'm...

334
00:25:28.440 --> 00:25:31.210
so weak!

335
00:25:31.210 --> 00:25:32.480
It's Garp!

336
00:25:31.310 --> 00:25:35.850
<b>Windmill Village, Kingdom of Goa, East Blue</b>

337
00:25:32.480 --> 00:25:34.820
Garp's returned on his battleship!

338
00:25:34.820 --> 00:25:35.880
On business?!

339
00:25:36.220 --> 00:25:39.040
Garp, we read all about the war!

340
00:25:39.040 --> 00:25:41.030
A resounding Marine victory, right?!

341
00:25:41.030 --> 00:25:43.280
Yeah, and everyone here is safe?

342
00:25:43.280 --> 00:25:44.820
Is Luffy okay?!

343
00:25:44.820 --> 00:25:49.400
With Whitebeard dead, what'll happen
to the world?! Tell us, Garp!

344
00:25:49.400 --> 00:25:54.500
These past few days, we've seen
a lot of pirate ships on the open sea.

345
00:25:54.500 --> 00:25:58.770
The thought of being raided
keeps us up at night!

346
00:25:58.770 --> 00:26:03.970
Rest easy! I just sank
three of 'em on the way here.

347
00:26:03.970 --> 00:26:06.290
Really? That's good to hear!

348
00:26:06.290 --> 00:26:10.750
Amateurs like them don't know
their way around a fight!

349
00:26:10.750 --> 00:26:13.450
Although, Whitebeard was
a stabilizing factor...

350
00:26:13.450 --> 00:26:18.390
With him gone, every sea in the world
will become turbulent.

351
00:26:18.390 --> 00:26:23.020
Don't let your guard down just because
you live in a remote part of the East Blue.

352
00:26:23.020 --> 00:26:23.660
Hey!

353
00:26:23.660 --> 00:26:24.600
– Yes, sir!
– Yes, sir!

354
00:26:25.760 --> 00:26:29.010
"Security, courtesy of Marine HQ's
Vice Admiral Garp," huh?

355
00:26:29.010 --> 00:26:30.830
That's so reassuring!

356
00:26:30.830 --> 00:26:33.740
There's nothing to be afraid of now!

357
00:26:33.740 --> 00:26:36.740
Garp, we have another problem.

358
00:26:36.740 --> 00:26:41.950
Bandits came down out of the
mountains and took over Makino's bar!

359
00:26:41.950 --> 00:26:43.150
Bandits?

360
00:26:43.150 --> 00:26:45.480
Stop! Don't!

361
00:26:49.900 --> 00:26:51.200
Hey, Garp!

362
00:26:51.200 --> 00:26:52.590
Oh, that's her!

363
00:26:54.690 --> 00:26:58.060
You've got some nerve
showing your face here again!

364
00:26:59.290 --> 00:27:01.140
Garp!

365
00:27:01.140 --> 00:27:02.390
B-Boss!

366
00:27:02.390 --> 00:27:03.600
Vice Admiral Garp!

367
00:27:10.550 --> 00:27:13.780
Stand down! I know her.

368
00:27:16.170 --> 00:27:17.990
You...

369
00:27:18.620 --> 00:27:21.300
You were right there on the battlefield!

370
00:27:22.230 --> 00:27:24.140
They were right in front of you!

371
00:27:24.140 --> 00:27:26.320
So, what the hell were you doing?!

372
00:27:26.320 --> 00:27:28.300
What the hell were you doing?!

373
00:27:28.300 --> 00:27:30.840
Why?! Why?! Why?!

374
00:27:30.840 --> 00:27:33.100
Why?! Why?!

375
00:27:41.010 --> 00:27:44.510
Why did you just stand there and let Ace die?!

376
00:27:45.150 --> 00:27:48.480
Is duty more important than your family?!

377
00:27:48.480 --> 00:27:51.940
Right, Garp?! And they
call you the Hero of the Marines!

378
00:27:51.940 --> 00:27:53.830
Shrivel up and die, you geezer!

379
00:27:53.830 --> 00:27:56.200
Take it easy, boss! That's too far!

380
00:27:56.200 --> 00:27:57.090
– Boss...
– Boss...

381
00:27:57.090 --> 00:28:00.520
Garp, cat got your tongue?!
You could have saved him!

382
00:28:00.520 --> 00:28:02.360
Why didn't you do something?!

383
00:28:02.590 --> 00:28:05.030
Stand up! Get on your feet!

384
00:28:05.030 --> 00:28:08.530
You inhuman filth!

385
00:28:09.270 --> 00:28:11.100
That's enough, Dadan!

386
00:28:17.380 --> 00:28:18.880
Makino...

387
00:28:36.860 --> 00:28:41.400
They may have been within arm's reach,
but there was nothing he could do!

388
00:28:41.400 --> 00:28:43.630
The one hurting most here is Garp!

389
00:28:54.160 --> 00:28:55.710
Y-You're wrong...

390
00:28:58.020 --> 00:28:59.350
You're wrong...

391
00:29:00.820 --> 00:29:02.790
You're wrong!

392
00:29:03.560 --> 00:29:07.520
Luffy's the one who's hurting most!

393
00:29:17.240 --> 00:29:21.880
Now, try to imagine that he's
right here in front of you.

394
00:29:21.880 --> 00:29:25.190
I'm Ace! Who the hell are you?

395
00:29:25.190 --> 00:29:29.010
Bzzt! That's a no-go.
"Who the hell" is too rude.

396
00:29:29.770 --> 00:29:32.040
Is it, "Oh, it's you?!"

397
00:29:33.010 --> 00:29:34.590
Give me your name.

398
00:29:34.590 --> 00:29:35.990
Bzzt!

399
00:29:35.990 --> 00:29:37.720
And just who are you?

400
00:29:37.720 --> 00:29:39.060
Bzzt!

401
00:29:39.850 --> 00:29:41.990
Is it, "Who's that?"

402
00:29:41.990 --> 00:29:43.030
Bzzt! Bzzt!

403
00:29:44.370 --> 00:29:47.330
All wrong. Are you even trying?

404
00:29:47.550 --> 00:29:50.440
It's because you keep
distracting me with dumb stuff!

405
00:29:50.440 --> 00:29:51.720
Quit it!

406
00:29:51.720 --> 00:29:53.070
Hey, Ace!

407
00:29:53.070 --> 00:29:58.430
Yesterday, I found the nest of a giant snake,
and it was filled with humongous eggs!

408
00:29:58.430 --> 00:30:00.080
Let's go get them!

409
00:30:00.080 --> 00:30:02.340
Huh? Humongous eggs?

410
00:30:02.340 --> 00:30:04.490
No, not right now!

411
00:30:04.490 --> 00:30:07.280
I'm studying how to greet people!

412
00:30:07.280 --> 00:30:11.180
It'll be real bad if that giant snake
catches me when I go by myself!

413
00:30:11.180 --> 00:30:14.540
But I'll be fine if you're with me. C'mon!

414
00:30:14.540 --> 00:30:15.760
Shut up!

415
00:30:18.340 --> 00:30:22.570
You have to know how much
he looked up to his brother!

416
00:30:32.000 --> 00:30:32.510
Makino!

417
00:30:35.800 --> 00:30:37.080
Garp...

418
00:30:37.640 --> 00:30:42.620
What happened with Luffy?
The newspapers say he's gone missing.

419
00:30:42.620 --> 00:30:43.590
Mayor...

420
00:30:50.100 --> 00:30:52.210
He escaped in a submarine.

421
00:30:53.700 --> 00:30:59.490
Marines pursued him with everything they had
and conducted a thorough search.

422
00:30:59.490 --> 00:31:02.110
But no shipwreck was found.

423
00:31:03.140 --> 00:31:06.180
At least for now... he's alive!

424
00:31:07.460 --> 00:31:08.510
Thank goodness!

425
00:31:08.510 --> 00:31:14.900
So, how's Marine Vice Admiral Garp
connected to this mountain bandit?

426
00:31:14.900 --> 00:31:15.700
Who knows?

427
00:31:21.330 --> 00:31:23.910
Luffy might be an idiot,

428
00:31:23.910 --> 00:31:28.270
but no matter what kind of pirate
he becomes, I will always stand beside him.

429
00:31:30.700 --> 00:31:35.670
When I think about how he must be feeling,
it's like my heart is getting torn in half.

430
00:31:44.010 --> 00:31:47.280
Luffy!

431
00:31:47.280 --> 00:31:53.060
Don't you dare let this stop you!

432
00:31:57.600 --> 00:32:00.350
Now, we take a look far away...

433
00:32:00.350 --> 00:32:04.700
to somewhere in the second half
of the Grand Line, the New World.

434
00:32:29.520 --> 00:32:31.110
Red Hair...

435
00:32:33.120 --> 00:32:35.770
How can I thank you for this?

436
00:32:37.070 --> 00:32:39.820
Don't be ridiculous.

437
00:32:39.820 --> 00:32:43.670
He may have been my enemy,
but Whitebeard was a man worthy of respect.

438
00:32:44.750 --> 00:32:47.410
Even Sengoku thought so.

439
00:32:49.210 --> 00:32:52.480
Well, it's time we parted ways.

440
00:32:52.480 --> 00:32:54.350
Yeah. Thanks.

441
00:32:55.300 --> 00:32:59.320
Luffy, this must be difficult for you.

442
00:33:00.210 --> 00:33:04.070
Word of Ace's final moments
took me by surprise.

443
00:33:04.790 --> 00:33:07.530
Take back what you just said!

444
00:33:07.530 --> 00:33:11.100
Don't you dare mock the man who saved me!

445
00:33:11.100 --> 00:33:15.010
This era will be named after Whitebeard!

446
00:33:19.690 --> 00:33:21.650
His actions were just like...

447
00:33:22.890 --> 00:33:24.850
Captain Roger's.

448
00:33:27.220 --> 00:33:32.560
I sometimes wished the captain would retreat.

449
00:33:33.310 --> 00:33:35.380
I wished he would cry.

450
00:33:40.470 --> 00:33:42.770
Listen to me, Luffy.

451
00:33:43.110 --> 00:33:49.000
When you experience both victory and defeat,
and when you flee from battle and shed tears,

452
00:33:49.390 --> 00:33:52.170
that is when you grow into a man.

453
00:34:03.100 --> 00:34:05.590
It's okay to cry.

454
00:34:07.760 --> 00:34:09.620
Overcome this!

455
00:34:16.400 --> 00:34:20.420
<b>Isle of Women, Calm Belt</b>

456
00:34:25.380 --> 00:34:30.110
Dammit! I'm so weak! I can't protect anyone!

457
00:34:30.110 --> 00:34:31.400
Luffy.

458
00:34:32.420 --> 00:34:34.010
Go away!

459
00:34:35.160 --> 00:34:37.190
Leave me alone!

460
00:34:37.190 --> 00:34:42.890
I can't do that! I can't stand
to let you hurt yourself further!

461
00:34:44.420 --> 00:34:47.100
It's my body! I'll decide what I do with it!

462
00:34:47.540 --> 00:34:51.400
Then by the same token,
Ace's body was also his own...

463
00:34:51.400 --> 00:34:53.870
His death was his decision!

464
00:34:53.870 --> 00:34:56.140
Just shut the hell up!

465
00:34:56.140 --> 00:34:58.680
One more word, and I'll kick your ass!

466
00:34:58.680 --> 00:35:01.910
You're welcome to try
if it'll make you feel better!

467
00:35:02.360 --> 00:35:07.850
I, too, am injured... but I won't
lose to you! Not as you currently are!

468
00:35:08.100 --> 00:35:09.580
Gum-Gum...

469
00:35:09.980 --> 00:35:11.960
Pistol!

470
00:35:36.170 --> 00:35:38.020
Jinbe...

471
00:35:38.990 --> 00:35:41.970
While I was out chasing Teach...

472
00:35:43.360 --> 00:35:48.610
I met my little brother for the first time
in three years in the Kingdom of Alabasta.

473
00:35:49.330 --> 00:35:53.330
As soon as I saw him, I felt relieved.

474
00:35:55.210 --> 00:35:57.100
Do you know why?

475
00:36:02.730 --> 00:36:05.480
Ow! That hurts!

476
00:36:07.180 --> 00:36:10.780
I said that hurts, you punk!

477
00:36:15.850 --> 00:36:19.520
Did you lose sight of everything?!

478
00:36:19.520 --> 00:36:23.060
You believed that you
could overcome anything!

479
00:36:23.060 --> 00:36:26.000
And you never doubted your strength!

480
00:36:26.630 --> 00:36:32.110
But a horde of enemies ruthlessly shattered your
beliefs and rendered you unable to do a thing...

481
00:36:32.110 --> 00:36:35.100
And your brother was your
guiding light on this sea!

482
00:36:35.100 --> 00:36:37.610
You've lost so much...

483
00:36:37.610 --> 00:36:43.360
The world itself has become your
greatest obstacle yet, blocking your vision!

484
00:36:45.000 --> 00:36:47.840
You can no longer see the path forward!

485
00:36:47.840 --> 00:36:50.790
Dark clouds of regret and guilt consume you!

486
00:36:51.480 --> 00:36:54.340
Your pain overwhelms you, Luffy,

487
00:36:54.340 --> 00:36:56.260
but put an end those feelings!

488
00:36:56.740 --> 00:36:59.560
Stop dwelling on what you've lost!

489
00:37:00.120 --> 00:37:02.200
What's gone is gone!

490
00:37:02.200 --> 00:37:06.150
What is it that you still have?!

491
00:37:54.120 --> 00:37:57.560
Luffy, don't mess around up here!

492
00:37:57.560 --> 00:37:59.190
My regimen needs focus!

493
00:38:04.160 --> 00:38:07.660
Luffy, hurry and get everyone into position!

494
00:38:07.660 --> 00:38:09.500
There's a storm ahead!

495
00:38:11.090 --> 00:38:16.040
Just you wait and see, Luffy!
I'm gonna catch a big one soon!

496
00:38:19.350 --> 00:38:23.110
Luffy, it's almost done. Be patient and wait!

497
00:38:24.280 --> 00:38:28.280
Luffy, no matter the injury,
you're in good hands!

498
00:38:28.280 --> 00:38:30.920
I'll always fix you up, good as new!

499
00:38:35.100 --> 00:38:36.460
Oh, Luffy.

500
00:38:37.020 --> 00:38:40.760
If you're interested, I can
teach you about archeology.

501
00:38:43.590 --> 00:38:48.520
Hey, Luffy! The cola engine
is purring like a kitten today!

502
00:38:49.580 --> 00:38:52.540
You can leave everything
about the Sunny to me!

503
00:38:53.300 --> 00:38:57.770
Good morning, Luffy! Rise and shine!

504
00:38:57.770 --> 00:39:00.580
Well then, let's get started
with a morning ditty!

505
00:39:08.020 --> 00:39:09.660
Luffy.

506
00:39:09.660 --> 00:39:11.360
Luffy!

507
00:39:11.360 --> 00:39:13.070
Luffy!

508
00:39:13.070 --> 00:39:14.770
Luffy.

509
00:39:14.770 --> 00:39:16.470
Luffy!

510
00:39:16.470 --> 00:39:18.170
Luffy.

511
00:39:18.170 --> 00:39:19.870
Luffy!

512
00:39:19.870 --> 00:39:21.810
Luffy!

513
00:39:22.050 --> 00:39:23.770
– Luffy!
– Luffy!

514
00:39:35.810 --> 00:39:37.790
My crew...

515
00:39:37.980 --> 00:39:40.380
I still have my crew!

516
00:39:40.380 --> 00:39:42.670
Zoro! Nami! Usopp!

517
00:39:42.670 --> 00:39:45.260
Sanji! Chopper! Robin!

518
00:39:45.260 --> 00:39:47.700
Franky! Brook!

519
00:39:47.700 --> 00:39:49.730
I still have my friends!

520
00:39:52.280 --> 00:39:53.370
I see.

521
00:39:54.900 --> 00:39:58.140
We promised to meet up somewhere.

522
00:39:58.780 --> 00:40:01.780
Guys, meet back at the Sunny in three days!

523
00:40:01.780 --> 00:40:03.380
– Okay!
– Okay!

524
00:40:04.620 --> 00:40:06.350
I gotta get there...

525
00:40:06.350 --> 00:40:08.980
even though I'm running late.

526
00:40:08.980 --> 00:40:12.510
I'm sure they're all waiting for me!

527
00:40:13.510 --> 00:40:18.460
What I saw there... Jinbe...

528
00:40:20.920 --> 00:40:23.860
An older brother can't help worrying...

529
00:40:24.850 --> 00:40:26.940
about their kid brother.

530
00:40:27.470 --> 00:40:30.910
I'm sure he's been a handful...

531
00:40:31.150 --> 00:40:33.310
Take care of him for me.

532
00:40:34.380 --> 00:40:40.580
I saw that Luffy's no longer that kid
who couldn't help but follow me everywhere.

533
00:40:40.850 --> 00:40:42.860
You see now...

534
00:40:45.340 --> 00:40:48.350
he has a crew he can rely on.

535
00:40:49.860 --> 00:40:53.060
No matter what happens, he'll be just fine.

536
00:40:53.610 --> 00:40:56.100
I was so relieved.

537
00:41:00.200 --> 00:41:02.710
I... wanna see them.

538
00:41:02.890 --> 00:41:06.980
I really wanna see them!
